PCA

Splitting: Tot = Train + Test

The PCA is fitted on Train, and Test will be the supplementary observations.

Here the splitting is provided by the dataset (= variable typ) but, alternatively, data Tot could be splitted a posteriori (e.g. random sampling, systematic sampling, etc.) 

s = Bool.(test)
## or: s = test .== 1
Xtrain = rmrow(Xp, s)
Ytrain = rmrow(Y, s)
Xtest = Xp[s, :]
Ytest = Y[s, :]
ntrain = nro(Xtrain)
ntest = nro(Xtest)
(ntot = ntot, ntrain, ntest)

(ntot = 4075, ntrain = 3701, ntest = 374)

Projection of Test in the Train score-space

Below function transform has to be qualified since both packages Jchemo and DataFrames export a function transform.

This will be the same with common function names such as predict, coef, etc.

Ttrain = fm.T
Ttest = Jchemo.transform(fm, Xtest)
